Isaac Asimov was a famous American writer and scientist known for his science fiction and popular science books. Born in Russia in 1920, he moved to the U.S. as a child. His most famous works include the “Foundation” series, which talks about the rise and fall of a space empire, and the “Robot” series, introducing the Three Laws of Robotics. He also wrote many popular science books that explained complex ideas in an easy-to-understand way.

Asimov had a Ph.D. in biochemistry and taught at Boston University. He wrote on a wide range of topics, including history and literature. His works continue to inspire and educate people. He won many awards and was named a Grand Master of Science Fiction. Asimov’s stories and books are still important and enjoyed by many today.
